From b167444c0cec6ee027a613e7f8723404a0ae84a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: paulhh <p.linnow@dp-planung.de>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 00:48:55 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] AccessibilityAnalysis: add public-transport (Valhalla
 multimodal) isochrones
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds an ÖPNV / public-transport profile mapped to Valhalla's multimodal
costing (walk + HVV GTFS transit). Multimodal is time-dependent, so the
request now attaches a date_time (local "depart at"). The UI button is
gated to the Valhalla backend (ORS has no transit) and restricted to the
time scale unit. i18n (de/en) + rangeSettings entry added.

Unit tests cover the costing map and the date_time present/absent paths
(9/9 pass, lint clean). Request shape matches a known-working Valhalla
multimodal isochrone example. Live end-to-end verification is pending a
transit-enabled Valhalla tileset (blocked on an upstream enhance-stage
bug, see BACKLOG §2).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
